ðŸŸ  Medium (Core Prefix Sum Techniques)


560. Subarray Sum Equals K
Count subarrays whose sum = k.
Key idea: prefix sum + hashmap of frequencies.


930. Binary Subarrays With Sum
Count subarrays with sum = s in binary array.
Key idea: identical to 560 with binary optimization.


523. Continuous Subarray Sum
Subarray sum is multiple of k.
Key idea: prefix sum modulo k + earliest index map.


525. Contiguous Array
Longest subarray with equal 0s and 1s.
Key idea: transform 0â†’-1; longest subarray with sum=0 (prefix hashmap first index).


238. Product of Array Except Self
Output product except self without division.
Key idea: prefix products + suffix products (classic).


1524. Number of Sub-arrays With Odd Sum
Count subarrays with odd total.
Key idea: prefix parity counts (#even, #odd).


1124. Longest Well-Performing Interval
Work hours > 8 vs â‰¤ 8.
Key idea: transform to +1/-1; longest subarray with positive sum using prefix + monotonic stack / earliest index map.


304. Range Sum Query 2D â€“ Immutable
2D prefix sums for rectangular queries.
Key idea: 2D prefix matrix to compute any rectangle sum in O(1).


1248. Count Number of Nice Subarrays
Exactly k odd numbers in subarray.
Key idea: prefix count of odds + hashmap of frequencies.


1658. Minimum Operations to Reduce X to Zero
Pick from ends; minimize picks.
Key idea: convert to longest subarray with sum = total - x (prefix + hashmap or two-pointer for non-negative).


1871. Jump Game VII (can be done via prefix of reachability windows)
Key idea: prefix of reachable counts to speed sliding window checks.



